<p class="documentDescription">Thank you for downloading Bika LIMS</p>

<div style="z-index:-1;float:right;margin:1em;"><a href="load_setup_data">Load setup data</a></div>

<h3 class="Subheading">Installation Verification</h3>

<p>Make sure the id-server process is running before trying to add anything to the database</p>

<p>The id-server process has to be running before the LIMS data can be added.</p>
<p>The id-server port used (default 8081) must not be the same as the Zope
port (default 8080) and must be specified in the Environment section of etc/zope.conf</p>
<p>Ensure write permissions are valid for the  ./var/log and ./var directories.

You can start the id-server with a script as below and run it in the background.
<pre>
PYTHON=/usr/bin/python  ## MODIFY FOR YOUR PYTHON 
#MODIFY FOR YOUR SOURCE DIRECTORY
$PYTHON bika3/bika/lims/scripts/id-server.py \
        -f var/id.counter -p 8081 T \
        -l var/log/idserver.log  -d var/idserver.pid
</pre>
<p>
To test if the ID Server is running, use a web browser on the
URL, eg <a href="http://localhost:8081">http://localhost:8081</a>  -- 
you should see an increasing integer count when you reload.
<p>

